Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

4xm1ruvkx3awxDECLARE job BINARY_INTEGER := :job; next_date TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :mydate; broken BOOLEAN := FALSE; job_name VARCHAR2(128) := :job_name; job_subname VARCHAR2(128) := :job_subname; job_owner VARCHAR2(128) := :job_owner; job_start TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :job_start; job_scheduled_start TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :job_scheduled_start; window_start TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :window_start; window_end TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :window_end; chain_id VARCHAR2(14) := :chainid; credential_owner VARCHAR2(128) := :credown; credential_name VARCHAR2(128) := :crednam; destination_owner VARCHAR2(128) := :destown; destination_name VARCHAR2(128) := :destnam; job_dest_id varchar2(14) := :jdestid; log_id number := :log_id; BEGIN DECLARE ename VARCHAR2(30); exec_task BOOLEAN; BEGIN -- check if tuning pack is enabled exec_task := prvt_advisor.is_pack_enabled( dbms_management_packs.TUNING_PACK); -- check if we are in a pdb, -- since auto sqltune is not run in a pdb IF (exec_task AND -- tuning pack enabled sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') <> 0 AND -- not in non-cdb sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') <> 1 ) THEN -- not in root exec_task := FALSE; END IF; -- execute auto sql tuning task IF (exec_task) THEN ename := dbms_sqltune.execute_tuning_task( 'SYS_AUTO_SQL_TUNING_TASK'); END IF; -- check whether we are in non-CDB or a PDB -- auto SPM evolve only runs in a non-CDB or a PDB, not the root. IF (sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') = 0 OR sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') > 2) THEN exec_task := TRUE; ELSE exec_task := FALSE; END IF; -- execute auto SPM evolve task IF (exec_task) THEN ename := dbms_spm.execute_evolve_task('SYS_AUTO_SPM_EVOLVE_TASK'); END IF; END; :mydate := next_date; IF broken THEN :b := 1; ELSE :b := 0; END IF; END;

Finding 2: CPU Usage
Impact is .53 active sessions, 12.19% of total activity.
--------------------------------------------------------
Time spent on the CPU by the instance was responsible for a substantial part
of database time.

Recommendation 1: Application Analysis
Estimated benefit is 3.67 active sessions, 84.14% of total activity.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Action
Look at the "Top SQL Statements" finding for SQL statements consuming
significant time on CPU. For example, the INSERT statement with SQL_ID
"gmckvyb17cuff" is responsible for 44% of CPU usage during the analysis
period.

Recommendation 2: Database Configuration
Estimated benefit is .53 active sessions, 12.19% of total activity.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Action
Consider not using the compression option for RMAN jobs. Alternatively,
consider slowing down RMAN activity, or scheduling RMAN jobs when user
activity is lower.


Finding 3: Sequence Usage
Impact is .43 active sessions, 9.76% of total activity.
-------------------------------------------------------
Sequence cache misses were consuming significant database time.

Recommendation 1: Application Analysis
Estimated benefit is .43 active sessions, 9.76% of total activity.
------------------------------------------------------------------
Action
Investigate application or look at top SQL to find hot sequences. Use a
larger cache size for those sequences. Try avoiding the use of the ORDER
setting if running RAC.


Finding 4: Undersized SGA
Impact is .24 active sessions, 5.57% of total activity.
-------------------------------------------------------
The SGA was inadequately sized, causing additional I/O or hard parses.
The value of parameter "sga_target" was "40960 M" during the analysis period.

Recommendation 1: Database Configuration
Estimated benefit is .13 active sessions, 2.92% of total activity.
------------------------------------------------------------------
Action
Increase the size of the SGA by setting the parameter "sga_target" to
46080 M.

Symptoms That Led to the Finding:
---------------------------------
Wait class "User I/O" was consuming significant database time.
Impact is .11 active sessions, 2.44% of total activity.


Finding 5: Unusual "Configuration" Wait Event
Impact is .2 active sessions, 4.5% of total activity.
-----------------------------------------------------
Wait event "enq: SQ - contention" in wait class "Configuration" was consuming
significant database time.

Recommendation 1: Application Analysis
Estimated benefit is .2 active sessions, 4.5% of total activity.
----------------------------------------------------------------
Action
Investigate the cause for high "enq: SQ - contention" waits. Refer to
Oracle's "Database Reference" for the description of this wait event.
Action
Look at the "Top SQL Statements" finding for SQL statements consuming
significant time on the "enq: SQ - contention" wait event. For example,
the INSERT statement with SQL_ID "gmckvyb17cuff" is responsible for 61%
of these waits.

Recommendation 2: Application Analysis
Estimated benefit is .2 active sessions, 4.5% of total activity.
----------------------------------------------------------------
Action
Investigate the cause for high "enq: SQ - contention" waits in Module
"osh@uwvm2vlpapp0021.p-dc.ba.uwv.nl (TNS V1-V3)".

Recommendation 3: Application Analysis
Estimated benefit is .2 active sessions, 4.5% of total activity.
----------------------------------------------------------------
Action
Investigate the cause for high "enq: SQ - contention" waits in Service
"SYS$USERS".

Recommendation 4: Application Analysis
Estimated benefit is .1 active sessions, 2.33% of total activity.
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Action

("name|mode") value "1397817348" and P2 ("object #") value "127272".

Impact is .17 active sessions, 3.85% of total activity.

Wait class "Concurrency" was consuming significant database time.

select
dos."ID" as DOSSIER_ID
, dos."KEY"
, dos.AFG_BSN
, dos.UZS_VOLGNUMMER
, nvl(dos."COOKBOOKFK",dos."KEY") as COOKBOOKFK
, dos."COOKBOOKVALUEFK"
, dos."VALUE"
, dosdat.DATUM_ANTWOORD
, case when ref.VERVANGENDE_WAARDE_IND = 'Ja'
then 'Gevuld'
when dos."KEY" = 'gender' and dos."VALUE" = 'F'
then 'Vrouw'
when dos."KEY" = 'gender' and dos."VALUE" = 'M'
then 'Man'
when dos."KEY" = 'gender'
then 'Gender neutraal'
when dos."KEY" is not NULL
then dos."VALUE"
when dos."COOKBOOKVALUEFK" is not NULL
then cook."TITEL"
else dos."VALUE"
end as ANTWOORD
, dos."SEQUENCE" as ANTWOORD_VOLGNUMMER
, dos.DIM_START_DATUM
, dos.DIM_EIND_DATUM
, dos.DIM_RECENT_IND
, dos.DIM_ARCHIEFVERNIETIGING_STATUS
from OKV_PEERCODE_PM.OKV_PEER_DOSSIER_HV dos
inner join
(
select
"ID" as DOSSIER_ID
, UZS_VOLGNUMMER
, AFG_BSN
, TRUNC(TO_TIMESTAMP("VALUE",'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS')) as
DATUM_ANTWOORD
from OKV_PEERCODE_PM.OKV_PEER_DOSSIER_HV
where "KEY" = 'response_at'
) dosdat
on dos."ID" = dosdat.DOSSIER_ID
and dos.UZS_VOLGNUMMER = dosdat.UZS_VOLGNUMMER
and dos.AFG_BSN = dosdat.AFG_BSN
left join
(
select
UUID as COOKBOOKVALUEFK
, "TITEL"
from OKV_PEERCODE_PM.OKV_PEER_COOKBOOK_HV
) cook
on dos.COOKBOOKVALUEFK = cook.COOKBOOKVALUEFK
left join
(
select
nvl(COOKBOOK_UUID, DOSSIER_KEY) as COOKBOOKFK
, VERVANGENDE_WAARDE_IND
from INT_PEER_PM.REF_PEER_TB
where COOKBOOK_UUID is not NULL
) ref
on nvl(dos."COOKBOOKFK",dos."KEY") = ref.COOKBOOKFK

"Cluster" waits for this segment.
Rationale
The I/O usage statistics for the object are: 0 full object scans, 700088
physical reads, 0 physical writes and 700088 direct reads.

Symptoms That Led to the Finding:
---------------------------------
Wait class "User I/O" was consuming significant database time.
Impact is .14 active sessions, 8.51% of total activity.


Finding 5: "Network" Wait Class
Impact is .04 active sessions, 2.25% of total activity.
-------------------------------------------------------
Wait class "Network" was consuming significant database time.

No recommendations are available.

Impact is .03 active sessions, 2.14% of total activity.
-------------------------------------------------------

database time.
Waits for "library cache: mutex X" amounted to 2% of database time.

No recommendations are available.
